data.title: BIMZELXÂ® shows sustained improvement in Hidradenitis Suppurativa - 48.2% had no draining tunnels at 1 year, 62.9% at 3 years.
data.description: The duration for reducing draining tunnels has been extended to three years. Among patients with at least one draining tunnel initially, 48.2% no longer had any after one year, and this percentage increased to 62.9% after three years. This sustained reduction indicates ongoing relief from symptoms related to these lesions. Additionally, for patients who had no draining tunnels initially, this count remained at zero for three years.

data.title: University of Denver to join West Coast Conference on July 1, 2026, enhancing academic and athletic opportunities.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, the University of Denver (DU) announced its acceptance of an invitation to join the West Coast Conference, effective from July 1, 2026. This move will see DU becoming a part of a prestigious conference alongside other reputable academic and athletic institutions.

data.title: New Irving Health and Wellness Clinic opening on Nov. 3, 2025, at 8200 N MacArthur Blvd, Suite 110, Irving, TX.
data.description: A new health and wellness clinic in Irving, Texas is set to open on November 3, 2025, located at 8200 N MacArthur Blvd, Suite 110, Irving, TX 75063. The clinic shares a building with the ER of Irving at the same address, but has separate entrances and suites.

data.title: Liberty Latin America aids Jamaica with hurricane relief post-Hurricane Melissa, airlifting crucial supplies within 48 hours.
data.description: In Denver, Colorado, Liberty Latin America Ltd., operating as NASDAQ: LILA and LILAK, along with OTC Link: LILAB, swiftly responded within 48 hours post the destructive Hurricane Melissa, by partnering with the Liberty Caribbean Foundation to deliver crucial aid to support Jamaica's recovery. Through the organization of a chartered X-Cargo A321 aircraft, essential supplies such as potable water, non-perishable food, and hygiene products were airlifted. The swift action aimed to assist in the restoration efforts following the disaster.

data.title: Boqii Holding Limited responds to unusual market activity, noting anomalous trading in its Class A shares on NYSE American.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Boqii Holding Limited, a prominent pet-focused platform in China, disclosed that it had observed unusual trading patterns in its Class A ordinary shares on the NYSE American LLC. The company, listed under the ticker symbol BQ, has recognized this irregular activity in the market.

data.title: Inventor from Ball Ground, Ga, creates Trinity Window Rain Guards to prevent rain entering windows for added airflow.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 31, 2025, an inventor from Ball Ground, Georgia, expressed the motivation behind creating the TRINITY WINDOW RAIN GUARDS, aimed at stopping rain from entering through open windows for increased airflow. The innovative window insert design serves a dual purpose by offering additional protection.

data.title: SAL expands internationally with TAM Group to boost air cargo ops between Saudi Arabia and China. #logistics #partnership
data.description: In Singapore on October 31, 2025, SAL Logistics Services, a top player in cargo handling, logistics solutions, and supply chain management in Saudi Arabia, has finalized a crucial partnership deal with TAM Group. This collaboration aims to enhance air cargo operations connecting China and Saudi Arabia, leveraging on their combined expertise and resources.

data.title: Zions Bancorporation board declares $0.45 quarterly dividend per common share, payable Nov 20.
data.description: Zions Bancorporation, N.A. (NASDAQ: ZION) headquartered in Salt Lake City disclosed on October 31, 2025, that its board of directors has approved a quarterly dividend of $0.45 per common share. This dividend is set to be disbursed on November 20, 2025, to shareholders of record at the mentioned date.

data.title: HTC and IngenioSpec settled ITC dispute on electronic eyewear products in WACO, Texas. #audio
data.description: A patent dispute regarding electronic eyewear technology has been successfully resolved between IngenioSpec and HTC in Waco, Texas. The resolution brings an end to the legal conflict surrounding the innovation. The specifics of the settlement, including any financial agreements or details regarding the technology in question, have not been disclosed to the public. This development marks a significant milestone for both companies involved and highlights the importance of protecting intellectual property in the tech industry.

data.title: DATTCO Smithfield bus teamsters ratify strong new 3-year contract with major gains in wages, health care, job protections, and retirement.
data.description: A new three-year agreement has been ratified by members at DATTCO Smithfield, represented by Teamsters Local 251 in Smithfield, Rhode Island on October 31, 2025. The agreement delivers substantial gains in wages, health care, job protections, and retirement benefits for employees. It has been widely approved by the members.
